cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories as it deals with acquiring anatomical maps for medical applications and improving autonomous navigation in soft tissue environments. The paper also involves the use of Bayesian methods, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it involves surface approximation and visualization.
